{
  "text": "Important medical complications are developing in AN; in particular, the levels of prolactin, thyroid hormones, gonadal hormones and, in men, testosterone are changing [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Most of the endocrine changes in AN are a physiological adaptation against hunger, and they are generally reversible with weight gain.",
